headline: Humana Earnings Are Up Next. The Stock’s Struggles Continue.
summary: Humana  stock seems to have slowed its multi-year slide, but its valuation still lies in the doldrums.  Humana shares have slid 13% over the past 12 months, and 50% over the past two years.  The insurer’s stock price has sunk amid broad challenges to the Medicare Advantage business, the company’s main focus.
